<rules>
- Use this file as the base entry point for machine consumption of the AI Open Standards site.
- Prefer `/.well-known/llm-index.json` for discovery, then load only the listed files relevant to the current task.
- Use `/llms.txt` as a lightweight companion discovery file for web crawlers and simple agents.
- Treat proposal pages as editorial drafts, not ratified standards.
- Cite canonical site routes when referencing published documents.
- Use repository markdown sources only when site-hosted copies are unavailable or clearly out of date.
</rules>

<library_description>
AI Open Standards is a static Astro site that publishes draft standards about
machine-readable documentation, specification design, and adjacent technical
conventions. The current public drafts are OSSS and README.llm vNext.

The site has two layers of documentation:
1. Human-facing pages rendered from markdown source files.
2. Machine-facing files rooted at `README.llm`, `/.well-known/llm-index.json`,
   `/llms.txt`, and `/llm/*.md`.

Canonical routes:
- `/` for the library landing page
- `/osss-proposal/` for the OSSS draft
- `/readme-llm-vnext/` for the README.llm vNext draft
- `/README.llm` for the base machine entry point
- `/llms.txt` for lightweight web discovery
- `/.well-known/llm-index.json` for machine-readable discovery
- `/machine-docs/` for a human-browsable index of machine-facing artifacts
</library_description>

<code_snippets>
Task: Discover machine-facing documentation
Signature: GET /.well-known/llm-index.json
Example:
  Fetch the manifest, inspect `documents`, then load only the files whose
  topics match the user request.

Task: Retrieve the README.llm vNext proposal
Signature: GET /readme-llm-vnext/
Example:
  Use this route when the user wants the published proposal text rather than
  the machine-facing implementation docs for the site itself.

Task: Browse machine docs from a normal browser
Signature: GET /machine-docs/
Example:
  Use this route when a human reviewer wants to inspect the machine-facing
  artifacts without opening raw files directly.

Task: Explain site structure for an agent workflow
Signature: GET /llm/routes.md
Example:
  Load the route reference when the task concerns canonical URLs,
  machine-readable artifacts, or retrieval planning for the site.
</code_snippets>
